scene.message:
Maki: That lady says the{nl}
strangest thing. She says too{nl}
much happiness makes her{nl}
uneasy.{waitkey}{clearbox}Every day being fun is the{nl}
best, isn't it? Don't you{nl}
think so?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: I won't ask for luxury,{nl}
but if only there were armor{nl}
marked "No. 1"...{waitkey}{clearbox}There's no such thing.{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Never mind.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: My mom's got the worst{nl}
taste in clothes!{waitkey}{clearbox}One time she bought me a{nl}
T-shirt with "Sukeroku"{nl}
written across the chest.{waitkey}{clearbox}Where does she even find{nl}
stuff like that!{waitkey}{clearbox}Ah{wait_fr:37}, I'm {wait_fr:21}not like, worried{nl}
about my mom or anything.{wait_fr:21}{nl}
Don't get the wrong idea.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Ayase likes it mini.{nl}
If it's too long, isn't it{nl}
kinda frumpy?{waitkey}{ret}

Townsperson: I'm happy to live{nl}
in such a fine town.{waitkey}{clearbox}But too much happiness, and{nl}
a person starts to feel{nl}
uneasy, you know.{waitkey}{clearbox}I start to think that when I{nl}
wake tomorrow, it'll all turn{nl}
out to have been a dream.{waitkey}{ret}

Boutique Clerk: Welcome~ What{nl}
are you looking for, hon? If{nl}
you like, I'll fit it to{nl}
your size!{waitkey}{ret}
